      • Public Function GetSelectedRowsInBwTable(bwt As BoardwalkTable) As Range

        Public Function GetSelectedRowsInBwTable(bwt As BoardwalkTable) As Range
        Details:

        '---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
        ' Procedure : GetSelectedRowsInBwTable
        ' Author : Sandhya Murkute
        ' Date : 6/13/2011
        ' Purpose : This function gets the entire boardwalk rows even if user has selected limited number of columns given the boardwalk table.
        ' Hence, user need not scroll horizontally to select entire boardwalk row.
        ' Even if the user selects limited number of columns, entire row can be retrieved against the selection.
        ' For example:
        ' Boardwalk table range = a10:m100
        ' User selected range = d15:h25
        ' Function returned range = a15:m25
        ' Parameters:
        ' * Boardwalk table--From which the selected rows are to be retrieved.
        ' Returns: Range
        ' * Row range--That constitutes all boardwalk columns.
        '------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------

      • Public Function GetSelectionInBWTable(bwt As BoardwalkTable, Optional bWithHeaderRange As Boolean = False) As Range

        Public Function GetSelectionInBWTable(bwt As BoardwalkTable, Optional bWithHeaderRange As Boolean = False) As Range
        Details:

        '---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
        ' Procedure : GetSelectionInBWTable
        ' Author : Siddhant Chothe
        ' Date : 2/22/2011
        ' Purpose : This function returns only that part of selected range which lies inside the boardwalk table range.
        ' Parameters:
        ' * Boardwalk table--The boardwalk table in which selection is looked up.
        ' * Include header flag--When true, checks selection in entire boardwalk table. When false, considers selection only in data area excluding the header range.
        ' Returns: Range
        ' * Range--Whenselection lies inside the range of boardwalk table.
        ' * Nothing--When the selection lies outside the boardwalk table.
        '------------- --------------------------------------------------------------------------
